Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.35,0:00:18.36,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.65,0:00:29.83,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.87,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.10,0:01:08.73,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.48,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.72,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.65,0:00:29.83,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.87,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.10,0:01:08.73,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.48,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.72,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.35,0:01:49.27,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 07 - Ben's Bad Luck
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.88,0:02:01.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! This was green wood, it makes too much smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.72,0:02:04.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We don't burn it because it burns cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.56,0:02:08.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And this fire's supposed to be bright!\NHow can you not know even that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.45,0:02:09.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.60,0:02:12.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We burn it so that dad and brother\Ncan spot it even from afar, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.77,0:02:15.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why you don't throw green wood\Ninto the fire, understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.93,0:02:18.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wah! So smoky!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.27,0:02:20.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But won't they be able\Nto also use smoke as a landmark?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.99,0:02:22.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's only in daytime!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.53,0:02:29.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! That's a terrible smoke you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.94,0:02:31.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know how to burn it better?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.81,0:02:33.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May just threw in some green wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.50,0:02:35.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and brother returned already?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:40.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I also tried looking for them on the coast,\Nbut still nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.38,0:02:45.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping we'd just missed each other on the road\Nand they're back home already...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.68,0:02:48.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think dad and brother may have gotten lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.77,0:02:51.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just hope they're fine and well, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.56,0:02:56.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Mr. Jamling injured his leg,\Nwhen he got lost on his way home from Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.65,0:02:58.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really sure they're fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.51,0:03:02.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the ones who rescued Mr. Jamling back then\Nwere dad and Ben, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.68,0:03:04.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's unlikely they'd make the same mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.98,0:03:07.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably right. I'm sure you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.38,0:03:10.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still nothing, even now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.16,0:03:11.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.87,0:03:13.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is Tob asleep already?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.42,0:03:16.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's asleep, and it's also time\Nfor you two to go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.87,0:03:18.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's way past your bedtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.72,0:03:20.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.19,0:03:23.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason for you to worry\Nabout dad and Ben, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.83,0:03:27.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back in England, he used to go out\Nfor a night stroll all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.49,0:03:29.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we're in Australia now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.12,0:03:33.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what difference does it make, Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:35.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At night, all places are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.12,0:03:40.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least, the moon may come out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.92,0:03:42.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.83,0:04:02.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful where you walk, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:03.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:04.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's speed up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.34,0:04:05.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.71,0:04:20.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! You two are still awake?\NThis won't do! Go to bed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.27,0:04:22.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.78,0:04:34.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.32,0:04:35.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.22,0:04:37.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.58,0:04:40.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way I can fall asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.17,0:04:45.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,God, please protect our dad and brother, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:49.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.02,0:04:49.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.90,0:04:53.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have this feeling we've been walking in circles for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.65,0:04:57.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be, we've been walking towards the shore all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.01,0:04:58.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.37,0:05:00.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.24,0:05:01.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.17,0:05:11.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's about time the moon comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.42,0:05:12.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.38,0:05:14.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With just the lamp's light,\Nwe can't really see all that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:17.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, does that mean we're lost after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.72,0:05:20.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I think we were probably\Non the correct path up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.58,0:05:23.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we should already be\Nout of the woods by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.10,0:05:24.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's also true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.81,0:05:28.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not walk further\Nuntil the moon comes out. Please, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.16,0:05:31.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, everyone is likely worried about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.75,0:05:33.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's best that we return as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.63,0:05:35.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we might get lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.38,0:05:37.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.20,0:05:39.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.46,0:05:41.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just bumped into a strange animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.50,0:05:42.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A strange animal?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.33,0:05:47.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.49,0:05:59.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem to be a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:00.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a wild boar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.76,0:06:04.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The animals living around here\Nare nothing like what we've seen in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:05.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.28,0:06:06.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.25,0:06:07.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, let's keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:08.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.05,0:06:09.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.01,0:06:10.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The moon is out, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.85,0:06:20.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.62,0:06:21.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.84,0:06:26.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Moonrise or no moonrise,\Nhe is not the kind to get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.34,0:06:29.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, there's no need to worry\Nabout dad and Ben, right, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.72,0:06:30.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.81,0:06:36.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny, Clara?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.39,0:06:41.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that a single glance at your face would be enough for anyone to tell how worried you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.47,0:06:42.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.58,0:06:45.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}am{\i0} glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:46.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.66,0:06:49.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really glad the moon decided to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.50,0:07:02.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:10.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can already hear the waves clearly from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.32,0:07:13.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, we're almost at the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.06,0:07:16.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think we may have strayed\Na little to the south from the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.31,0:07:19.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can now return safely\Nby going north along the coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.06,0:07:21.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we made it to here, that means our tents\Nare already near, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:22.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:47.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And she said she was worried\Nand couldn't get no sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.35,0:07:49.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad had returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.97,0:07:51.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You were awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:55.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I am!\NI'm so worried I can't get no sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.38,0:08:02.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're a skilled liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.34,0:08:10.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:16.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:19.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It must be some animal\Nthat only exists in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:24.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's a peculiar one...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:27.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! We don't have the time for detours!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.43,0:08:29.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.27,0:08:37.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.97,0:08:43.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.07,0:08:57.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure are peculiar guys. Both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.81,0:09:04.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep, Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:07.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be all right.\NWhy don't you go take a rest yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.75,0:09:10.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stop thinking that they should return soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.33,0:09:13.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have a feeling they won't return today either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:17.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if something unexpected\Nhappened to them in Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.84,0:09:22.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And if they haven't returned even this late,\Nit must be that nothing particularly good happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.93,0:09:28.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the time to succumb to brooding.\NWe'll know for sure when dad returns, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.36,0:09:32.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're probably right. No reason to worry\Nabout something ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.86,0:09:35.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.09,0:09:35.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.19,0:09:38.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've all come to Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.47,0:09:42.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,hoping that we'll be many times happier here\Nthan we were in England, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.99,0:09:44.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.82,0:09:46.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really believe this will come true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.23,0:09:49.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:52.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't sound very convinced, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.31,0:09:55.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm convinced in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:17.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We {\i1}will{\i0} become happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.90,0:10:19.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.03,0:10:23.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Had dad returned yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:26.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry I woke you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.54,0:10:31.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy isn't here yet.\NNow, don't you worry and go back to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.57,0:10:36.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! They're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.21,0:10:36.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.96,0:10:39.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, you're still half-asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.40,0:10:41.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom just said, "not yet," remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.75,0:10:43.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But they {\i1}are{\i0} back! Can't you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.77,0:10:44.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hear what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.10,0:10:46.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There! He's whistling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.98,0:10:48.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whistling?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.25,0:10:50.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's our brother's whistling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.58,0:10:52.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.22,0:10:58.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara, Lucy-May says she can hear Ben whistling...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.46,0:11:03.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the bonfire crackling is too loud here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.52,0:11:07.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You lied, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.05,0:11:08.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.29,0:11:10.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just admit it that you didn't hear no whistle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:13.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I heard it before!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.96,0:11:17.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody likes the liars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.56,0:11:19.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I never tell lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.54,0:11:26.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Looks like they're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:27.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.94,0:11:33.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:37.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's Ben right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.20,0:11:39.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.88,0:11:41.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.15,0:11:44.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:52.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're back, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.12,0:11:55.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home. But is sure is a little late.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.78,0:11:57.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A lot of things happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.57,0:11:59.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what were those things?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.76,0:12:01.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad will tell you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.27,0:12:03.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And why are you two still awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.85,0:12:05.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:08.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, brother, were you whistling while on the way here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.24,0:12:10.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but as we got closer, I stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:11.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There, heard it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.51,0:12:13.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't telling you no lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:14.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.72,0:12:17.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean "But still"?\NI demand an apology!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.20,0:12:19.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:21.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.71,0:12:23.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize, sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.35,0:12:25.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.59,0:12:28.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.58,0:12:31.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for giving you all that worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.75,0:12:33.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.37,0:12:34.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.91,0:12:36.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.25,0:12:37.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.10,0:12:44.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for making you all worry,\Nbut as you can see, we've returned safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.64,0:12:46.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's late, so everyone goes to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:48.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.46,0:12:50.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.34,0:12:51.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:53.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.82,0:12:55.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:13:03.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying my utmost to stay awake\Nand listen to dad's story with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.19,0:13:09.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But due to feeling so relieved,\Nas soon as I was in the bed, I ended up falling asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.88,0:13:14.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, honey,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.57,0:13:18.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,what do you say if we sell the prefabricated home\Nwe brought over from England?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.32,0:13:19.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.96,0:13:22.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're thinking of selling it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.13,0:13:23.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.15,0:13:28.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though I clearly heard dad\Nsaying he wants to sell the prefabricated home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.81,0:13:30.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.85,0:13:34.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No... it must have been a dream. Just a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.68,0:13:52.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good! We're done!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.17,0:13:59.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,On the next day,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.51,0:14:05.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,dad and Ben went to retrieve\Nthe rest of our things from the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.02,0:14:08.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we're all setting out for Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.44,0:14:21.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, put it on top of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.68,0:14:26.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Ben, I need you to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.22,0:14:28.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,See that our things\Ndon't get mixed with someone else's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:29.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.71,0:14:32.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, I'll make one more trip to the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:36.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No heavy stuff among our remaining things,\Nso I should be able to manage by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.13,0:14:38.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, an oxcart might arrive soon\Nto carry our things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.61,0:14:40.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,From Mr. Bard, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.98,0:14:44.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The precious oxcart\Nthat we barely managed to locate yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.63,0:14:48.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If not for that oxcart contract\Nwe concluded with with Mr. Bart,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:50.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,moving to Adelaide tomorrow\Nwould've been impossible for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.30,0:14:54.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, when Mr. Bart's oxcart arrives,\Nwe start loading our things onto it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.33,0:14:55.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.02,0:15:03.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.85,0:15:26.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, what's wrong?\NYou keep sighing so deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:27.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.55,0:15:28.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.46,0:15:31.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just feel disappointed, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.83,0:15:34.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still hung up on that prefabricated home?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.69,0:15:38.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I used to dream about how we come here\Nand live in that house ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.29,0:15:40.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it can't be helped since we can't take it to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.94,0:15:43.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like there's absolutely no way\Nfor us to take it there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.85,0:15:48.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It would take several days and a small fortune\Nto transport, isn't it what dad said?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.67,0:15:51.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's why, I guess,\NI have no choice but to give up on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.62,0:15:53.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.86,0:15:56.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And where's Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.99,0:15:59.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.64,0:16:02.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Sticky, start walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.39,0:16:13.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you taking that goat back to its owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.96,0:16:15.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.10,0:16:17.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Her owner hadn't appeared yet, Billy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.29,0:16:19.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you'll have two goats soon, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.44,0:16:21.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right. They'll be our goats.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.94,0:16:23.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Both she and her baby goat!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.39,0:16:25.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be born soon already!\NThat's what Mr. Parker told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.42,0:16:30.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And where are you taking her now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.22,0:16:33.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious? We're taking her\Nto where there's grass for eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.62,0:16:35.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Sticky, start walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.26,0:16:40.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You even gave her a name already!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.21,0:16:44.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.80,0:16:46.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.52,0:16:47.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:49.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.73,0:16:50.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.94,0:16:55.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Keep going, you lazy thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.98,0:16:57.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.27,0:17:07.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This much should be enough for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:12.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way! If she doesn't eat enough,\Nshe can't give birth to a healthy baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.25,0:17:13.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Positively horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.54,0:17:16.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.03,0:17:19.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That mister has been whipping\Nthe poor ox for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.53,0:17:23.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.53,0:17:25.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:28.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You wretch! Slacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.45,0:17:30.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like the cart is completely stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.37,0:17:31.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Should we help pushing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:32.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.56,0:17:36.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wretch! Slacker...! Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.35,0:17:35.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:42.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mister, we'll push the cart from behind,\Nbut you stop whipping the ox, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:49.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Slacker! Seems like you found\Nsome helpers here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:52.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Put some muscle, slacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:53.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Heavy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.03,0:17:56.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.43,0:18:01.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Like that! Good! Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.38,0:18:05.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.98,0:18:10.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.22,0:18:17.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mister, you're carrying\Nway too much stuff in that cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.98,0:18:21.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I can't throw it overboard either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.07,0:18:22.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.22,0:18:24.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Fresh water. They're gonna ferry it to the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.75,0:18:26.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Water for the ship, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.66,0:18:29.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey boy, sorry to bother,\Nbut could you push for a bit more?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.08,0:18:32.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just need to get it to the beach over there,\Nthe ship's crew will then come to fetch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:37.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't got no choice! We'll push.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.08,0:18:39.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're pushing, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.06,0:18:41.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:43.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.97,0:18:45.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.96,0:19:17.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.28,0:19:29.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, boy! If you got nothing better to do,\Ncould you give us a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.60,0:19:30.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:34.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:37.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take the barrels and roll them over there, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.81,0:19:40.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.34,0:19:43.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When you're done,\Nwe'll treat you to something tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.53,0:19:51.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! The current is sweeping away that barrel!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.08,0:19:56.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, that? Just forget about it,\Nit only had some flour in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.55,0:20:01.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But these here we can't afford losing.\NThey're for {\i1}this{\i0} business, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.41,0:20:04.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But for our family, flour is something\Nincredibly important!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.87,0:20:07.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've carried enough to the warehouse already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.44,0:20:10.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as "too much flour"!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.21,0:20:14.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, starting now, we'll be living\Nin the lands that have never been cultivated!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.09,0:20:18.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, boy, if you have that much energy\Nto pester us with it, why don't you go get it yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.94,0:20:22.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Will do just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:57.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it. Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.98,0:20:58.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.95,0:21:07.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right... That's way! Good! Good-good!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.87,0:21:10.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:20.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot, you two.\NIt seems, we finally made it to the destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.48,0:21:24.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Good Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.74,0:21:25.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:30.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, that right there\Nmust be our family's stuff, I swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.89,0:21:33.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That pile of things?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.36,0:21:35.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where my dad and brother are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.21,0:21:42.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.96,0:21:45.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they just dump it here and leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.12,0:21:47.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This looks like some fancy furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.01,0:21:49.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That, I don't know either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.52,0:21:53.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We have time until the evening\Nto ferry all that water to the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.35,0:21:56.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, the ship\Nis in a bit of a kerfuffle right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.52,0:22:01.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about this - if you don't have any urgent business,\Nwhy don't you hang out with us until the evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.52,0:22:03.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After this, my work would be concluded for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.80,0:22:08.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But tomorrow morning, I need to pick up\NMr. Popple's belonging and return to Adelaide again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.63,0:22:12.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that settles it. In that case,\Nlet's get to business straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.46,0:22:24.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,'Aight, pal. Your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.24,0:22:25.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.00,0:22:29.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Hey, the current carried that boy\Nway out into the open sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.33,0:22:30.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.47,0:22:35.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It ain't nothing to be worried about.\NThat boy said he likes flour, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.95,0:22:38.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And here's something we like very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.62,0:22:43.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it. Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.61,0:22:45.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.62,0:22:50.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is definitely my brother's shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.90,0:22:52.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And over here, he dropped his hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.92,0:22:57.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think he went for a swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.31,0:23:00.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Swimming is not among my brother's strong sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.75,0:23:01.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.82,0:23:06.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like someone's clutching a barrel!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.29,0:23:11.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Help me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.61,0:23:12.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.90,0:23:14.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't he shouting something?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.62,0:23:16.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could he be just playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.18,0:23:17.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.84,0:23:19.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you two looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.87,0:23:24.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our brother is all the way out there.\NSaying something to us, but we can't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.33,0:23:27.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.25,0:23:30.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He just said, "Help me please!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.93,0:23:32.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So he is drowning?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.24,0:23:34.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But he's still clutching onto that barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.16,0:23:36.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We need to find someone to help him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.44,0:23:36.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.77,0:23:39.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh cut it, you old wreck!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.53,0:23:41.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.32,0:23:45.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.20,0:23:48.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Save me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.91,0:24:07.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister and John found a Koala in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.57,0:24:09.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I absolutely insisted on catching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.71,0:24:13.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"The Eve of our Departure".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.11,0:24:14.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
